title: The Godfather: Part II
overview: The early life and career of Vito Corleone in 1920s New York City is portrayed, while his son, Michael, expands and tightens his grip on the family crime syndicate.

title: Death Note: Desu nôto
overview: A battle between the world's two greatest minds begins when Light Yagami finds the Death Note, a notebook with the power to kill, and decides to rid the world of criminals.

title: Funny Games
overview: Two violent young men take a mother, father, and son hostage in their vacation cabin and force them to play sadistic "games" with one another for their own amusement.

title: The Godfather
overview: An organized crime dynasty's aging patriarch transfers control of his clandestine empire to his reluctant son.

title: True Romance
overview: In Detroit, a lonely pop culture geek marries a call girl, steals cocaine from her pimp, and tries to sell it in Hollywood. Meanwhile, the owners of the cocaine, the Mob, track them down in an attempt to reclaim it.

title: Taxi Driver
overview: A mentally unstable veteran works as a nighttime taxi driver in New York City, where the perceived decadence and sleaze fuels his urge for violent action by attempting to liberate a presidential campaign worker and an underage prostitute.

title: L.A. Confidential
overview: As corruption grows in 1950s Los Angeles, three policemen - one strait-laced, one brutal, and one sleazy - investigate a series of murders with their own brand of justice.

title: Heat
overview: A group of professional bank robbers start to feel the heat from police when they unknowingly leave a clue at their latest heist.

title: Cool Hand Luke
overview: A laid back Southern man is sentenced to two years in a rural prison, but refuses to conform.

title: The Departed
overview: An undercover cop and a mole in the police attempt to identify each other while infiltrating an Irish gang in South Boston.

title: Blood Simple
overview: The owner of a seedy small-town Texas bar discovers that one of his employees is having an affair with his wife. A chaotic chain of misunderstandings, lies and mischief ensues after he devises a plot to have them murdered.

title: 12 Angry Men
overview: A jury holdout attempts to prevent a miscarriage of justice by forcing his colleagues to reconsider the evidence.

title: Bir Zamanlar Anadolu'da
overview: A group of men set out in search of a dead body in the Anatolian steppes.

title: Nightcrawler
overview: When Louis Bloom, a con man desperate for work, muscles into the world of L.A. crime journalism, he blurs the line between observer and participant to become the star of his own story.

title: Drishyam
overview: A man goes to extreme lengths to save his family from punishment after the family commits an accidental crime.

title: Dogville
overview: A woman on the run from the mob is reluctantly accepted in a small Colorado community in exchange for labor, but when a search visits the town she finds out that their support has a price.

title: À bout de souffle
overview: A small-time thief steals a car and impulsively murders a motorcycle policeman. Wanted by the authorities, he reunites with a hip American journalism student and attempts to persuade her to run away with him to Italy.

title: The Untouchables
overview: During the era of Prohibition in the United States, Federal Agent Eliot Ness sets out to stop ruthless Chicago gangster Al Capone and, because of rampant corruption, assembles a small, hand-picked team to help him.
stars: ['Kevin Costner', 'Sean Connery', 'Robert De Niro', 'Charles Martin Smith']

title: Wind River
overview: A veteran hunter helps an FBI agent investigate the murder of a young woman on a Wyoming Native American reservation.

title: A Bronx Tale
overview: A father becomes worried when a local gangster befriends his son in the Bronx in the 1960s.
